<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,655,680]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[342,532,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Liriomyza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="blechi">
<emphasis box="[342,532,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Liriomyza blechi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a widespread species with a characteristically striped scutum, and the unusual setal characters of sparsely haired eyes, inclinate posteromedial acrostichal setulae and a posteromedial seta on the mid tibia.
</paragraph>
